  "prompt": "Should organic peanut butter be refrigerated?",
  "response": "Organic peanut butter can differ from conventional peanut butter. Here are some guidelines:\n\n1. Natural/organic peanut butter without preservatives:\n- Should be refrigerated after opening\n- Refrigeration prevents oil separation and extends shelf life\n- Can become harder when cold, so you might want to let it sit at room temperature briefly before spreading\n\n2. Some organic peanut butters with added stabilizers:\n- May be okay to store at room temperature\n- Check the label for specific storage instructions\n\n3. General recommendation:\n- If the jar says \"refrigerate after opening,\" do so\n- If oil separation occurs, stirring and refrigeration can help maintain consistency\n\nAlways check the specific product's label for the most accurate storage instructions.",
